# Generated by agent-bridge install/upgrade — do not edit by hand.
#
# Authorizes the named controller user to restart its own daemon under
# sudo so PAM/initgroups rebuilds the supplementary-group set for the
# new daemon process. This is required after `usermod -aG <agent-group>`
# adds the controller to a per-agent group (agent create / isolate),
# because already-running processes (the daemon, forked from a shell
# whose group set was captured pre-usermod) cannot pick up the new
# supplementary group via SIGHUP — the kernel only refreshes credentials
# on the next initgroups() call, which happens during sudo's PAM setup.
#
# Authorize the ABSOLUTE bash binary path + the EXACT daemon command
# + EXACT arguments. Do not use `env` as the sudo command (authorizes
# /usr/bin/env broadly) and do not use a `restart *` wildcard
# (authorizes any restart arg shape). See codex r3 spec §1, §2 at
# /tmp/agb-6270-l2-variant3a-r3.md for rationale.
#
# SETENV is required so the matching --preserve-env=... list on the
# sudo invoke is honored. The preserved env vars are limited to the
# BRIDGE_* set the daemon needs to restart against the correct install.
#
# File path:   /etc/sudoers.d/agent-bridge-daemon-refresh-<controller_user>-<runtime_id>
# Mode:        0440 root:root
# Installed via: agent-bridge init sudoers daemon-refresh --apply
# Validated via: visudo -cf
#
# Two authorized commands:
#
#  1. `bridge-daemon.sh restart --force --internal-reason=group-refresh`
#     Used by `bridge_daemon_refresh_after_group_membership_change` to
#     restart the daemon under sudo/PAM when systemd is NOT managing
#     the daemon (launchd / non-Linux / explicit --no-sudo-self). r3
#     contract.
#
#  2. `bridge-daemon.sh run`
#     r4 follow-up — used by the sudo-wrapped systemd ExecStart so
#     every systemd-driven daemon start crosses the same sudo/PAM
#     refresh boundary. Without this entry the systemd-user manager
#     (whose own supp set is captured at login and never refreshed)
#     would launch sudo only for it to be rejected by sudoers policy,
#     leaving the daemon down. See codex r4 spec at
#     /tmp/agb-6281-l2-r4-systemd.md.
#
# No wildcards. No /usr/bin/env. Both Cmnds go through the same
# SETENV preserve-env list configured on the respective invocations.
{{controller_user}} ALL=({{controller_user}}) NOPASSWD: SETENV: {{bash_abs}} {{bridge_home_abs}}/bridge-daemon.sh restart --force --internal-reason=group-refresh
{{controller_user}} ALL=({{controller_user}}) NOPASSWD: SETENV: {{bash_abs}} {{bridge_home_abs}}/bridge-daemon.sh run
